BioLadder.org is an interactive tree of life viewer and wiki, 
and is open source under the GPL-V3 License. 

It is hosted at:
http://bioladder.org/
https://code.google.com/p/bioladder/


The Code:
To run it yourself, you need a web server, PHP and a MySQL Database.
You can get a combo install of all of them at:
http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp.html

Once you have those, make sure you have the code checked out in the 
root directory that is being hosted, and they should work.

There are two parts of the project:
1) wiki directory, which contains a mediawiki with symantic wiki
2) viewer directory, which contains a Sencha 2.1 app (only works 
   with Safari and Chrome, when 2.2 comes out, that is supposed 
   to work with IE10)